data.title: Xilio Therapeutics to present Phase 2 data for Vilastobart at SITC 40th Annual Meeting, highlighting response rate in MSS mCRC patients with high plasma tumor mutational burden.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, WALTHAM, Massachusetts - Xilio Therapeutics, Inc. (Nasdaq: XLO), a biotech company, revealed plans to present a late-breaking poster on vilastobart, a tumor-activated, Fc-enhanced anti-CTLA-4 therapy at the Society for Immunotherapy of Cancer (SITC) 40th Annual Meeting in National Harbor, Maryland from November 5-9, 2025. The poster will feature Phase 2 findings showcasing the response rate of vilastobart in conjunction with atezolizumab among patients with microsatellite stable (MSS) metastatic colorectal cancer (mCRC) and high plasma tumor mutational burden.

data.title: Tetra Tech wins £17M water engineering design contract for Portsmouth Water in Southern England to enhance services.
data.description: Tetra Tech, a prominent firm in consulting and engineering services for water, environment, and sustainable infrastructure, has been chosen by Portsmouth Water for engineering design and technical assistance to enhance water service provision to customers in Southern England. This partnership aims to help the company meet new regulatory goals. Tetra Tech, listed on NASDAQ as TTEK, will offer its expertise to design innovative solutions for improving water services in the region.

data.title: APS to build Desert Sun Power Plant, new natural gas facility, to meet Arizona's growing needs.
data.description: In Phoenix, Arizona, a new natural gas facility called the Desert Sun Power Plant is set to be constructed by Arizona Public Service. This development is aimed at catering to the increasing energy demands in the area. The facility is expected to contribute significantly to the state's energy infrastructure and is crucial in meeting the growing power needs of Arizona.

data.title: Ampere & Stratus Materials collaborate for cobalt-free cathode for Renault EVs in a new Joint Development Agreement.
data.description: A joint development agreement has been signed between Stratus Materials and Ampere in Boulogne-Billancourt, France, and Pittsburgh. The agreement is aimed at developing and confirming cobalt-free cathode technology for Renault Group.

data.title: Cullen/Frost reported Q3 2025 net income of $172.7M (up from $144.8M in Q3 2024). Loans increased $1.4B to $21.5B. Dividend declared $1.00 per common share. Stock symbol: CFR. Full details on Benzinga.com.
data.description: Cullen/Frost Bankers, Inc. declared a Q4 dividend of $1.00 per common share and $11.125 per Series B Preferred Stock. In Q3 2025, they reported a net income of $172.7 million, up from $144.8 million in Q3 2024. Average loans increased to $21.5 billion, deposits to $42.1 billion. Net interest income was $463.7 million, non-interest income $125.6 million. Non-interest expenses were $352.5 million. Credit loss expenses were $6.8 million, and net loan charge-offs were $6.6 million. The company will host a conference call on October 30, 2025 to discuss these results. They have $52.5 billion in assets as of September 30, 2025.

data.title: GigaMedia reported Q3 2025 revenues of $0.92 million with a net loss of $0.97 million. Cash & equivalents amounted to $29.4 million.
data.description: GigaMedia Limited released its unaudited financial results for the third quarter of 2025 reporting revenues of $0.92 million, a gross profit of $0.46 million, an operating loss of $1.00 million, and a net loss of $0.97 million. Revenues increased by 5.5% from the previous quarter and 19.1% year-over-year. The company aims to focus on developing products and services closely aligning with customer needs in the upcoming quarter. GigaMedia's cash, cash equivalents, and restricted cash stood at $29.4 million as of September 30, 2025. The CEO, James Huang, stated plans for internal growth, effective marketing, and expansion of the customer base. EBITDA was -$1.37 million, and the net asset value was around $3.51 per share. The non-GAAP measure used was EBITDA as a supplemental performance metric. Investors can inquire via email for Q&A regarding the quarterly performance. GigaMedia is a digital entertainment services provider based in Taiwan and Hong Kong. The forward-looking statements indicate expectations for future performance and strategic plans. Risk factors may affect actual results. Detailed financial statements and further company information can be accessed at gigamedia.com.tw.

data.title: Owlet's Dream Sight baby monitor is the first to receive SGS Cybersecurity Mark, certified by Brightsight, indicating high cybersecurity.
data.description: In Lehi, Utah, Owlet, Inc. unveiled its latest baby monitor, Dream Sight, as the inaugural baby monitor to secure the SGS Cybersecurity Mark, demonstrating superior international cybersecurity and privacy practices. The Company, traded on NYSE as OWLT, is known for innovating smart infant monitoring solutions. The certification was granted after a thorough evaluation by Brightsight, an SGS affiliate renowned for cybersecurity assessments. This milestone sets Dream Sight apart as a leading choice for parents seeking reliable and secure monitoring for their infants.
